<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 3:25PM CDT  by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Leon County through
415 PM CDT...
At 324 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a pair of strong
thunderstorms. One was located 6 miles north of Centerville, and the
other was 17 miles south of Buffalo. Movement was south at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
One of the storms will cross Interstate 45 between Buffalo and
Centerville. This includes Interstate 45 between mile markers 152
and 175.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
